

#  PROJECT GOAL

Build a web chatbot that:
 Answers SAP Business One questions
 Retrieves simulated company data (customers, orders, stock, invoices)
 Acts like an intelligent assistant for staff
 Uses OpenAI API (no JSON prompt training)
 Runs on free frontend + backend hosting

Think of it as a **virtual SAP assistant for employees**.

---

#  CORE SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE

#  Frontend (User Interface)

Users chat with the AI.

Tech stack (free & simple):

* HTML + CSS + Bootstrap
* JavaScript (fetch API)


UI features

* Chat window like WhatsApp
* Login (role-based: sales, inventory, finance)
* Quick buttons (Check stock, Find customer, Sales report)
* Conversation history
* Typing indicator

---

#  Backend (AI + SAP Logic)

This is the brain.

Tech stack 

* Node.js (Express) 
* OpenAI API integration
* MySQL database 

---

  Data Layer (Simulated SAP Data)

Since you’re simulating internet records for Crown Paints, create tables that mimic SAP Business One.

 customers
 items
 sales_orders
 invoices
 inventory
 employees
warehouses

This lets AI answer real business questions.

---

  AI CAPABILITIES (REAL FEATURES)

 💬 1. Natural Language Understanding

User types normally:

> “Show low stock items”
> “Customer balance for ABC Traders”
> “Today’s sales total”

Backend sends the question to OpenAI API with system instructions about Crown Paints operations.



 2. SAP Business Knowledge Mode

AI understands SAP concepts like:

* Business partners
* Sales orders
* A/R invoices
* Inventory valuation
* Purchase orders
* Stock transfers

You define this knowledge in the system prompt.

---

 3. Smart Query Engine

AI decides:
✔ When to answer normally
✔ When to fetch database data
✔ When to summarize reports

Example logic:

User → “Show top 5 selling paints this month”
Backend → Query database
AI → Explain results in human language

---

 📁 4. Company Context Awareness

AI always knows:

* It works for Crown Paints Limited
* Business type: paint manufacturing & distribution
* Departments: sales, warehouse, finance
* Products: emulsions, primers, gloss paints

This makes responses feel realistic and professional.

---

 5. Business Reporting Mode

AI generates:

* Sales summaries
* Inventory alerts
* Customer insights
* Financial explanations

Example:

> “Sales increased 12% this week due to bulk orders from distributors.”

---

### 🔐 6. Role-Based Intelligence

Different users get different answers.

Sales staff → customers & orders
Warehouse → inventory
Finance → invoices & balances

---

# 🔌 OPENAI API INTEGRATION FLOW

### Step 1 — User sends message

Frontend → backend API

### Step 2 — Backend builds AI instruction

System context includes:

* SAP Business One assistant role
* Crown Paints company data
* Allowed actions

### Step 3 — Backend calls OpenAI API

AI generates response or query intent.

### Step 4 — Backend fetches database info (if needed)

### Step 5 — AI formats final business response

### Step 6 — Response returned to chat UI

---

# 🧪 SIMULATED BUSINESS DATA YOU SHOULD CREATE

### Customers

| Name | Credit Limit | Balance | Region |

### Inventory

| Item Code | Product Name | Warehouse | Stock |

### Sales Orders

| Order No | Customer | Date | Total |

### Invoices

| Invoice No | Customer | Status | Amount |

This makes the chatbot feel like a real SAP system.

